    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-28T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-28T10:00:00-05:00" n="605"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d605">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">651.5231/167: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-28T15:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 28, 1935—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 28—12:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>81. Recent exchange agreement with France<note n="38" xml:id="d605fn38">Signed at
                        Madrid, December 21, 1935, League of Nations Treaty Series, vol. <hi
                            rend="smallcaps">clxvii</hi>, p. 65.</note> summarized Commercial
                    Attaché’s financial report week ended December 21st<note n="39"
                        xml:id="d605fn39">Not found in Department files.</note> will obviously
                    result in further increasing dollar remittances delay. Moreover confidential
                    official information just obtained that Spain has offered England clearing
                    agreement. Saw Sub-Secretary this morning who states exchange situation is
                    covered in pending commercial agreement of which we still have no copy and adds
                    that Spain is studying every means including that of loan to normalize exchange
                    with all countries.</p>
                <p>In view of the above developments believe early successful conclusion our
                    agreement more desirable than ever.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
